#- §6      ,,True Value"§r

§0My thoughts about the non-monetary value§r
§0        of money§r




§0        Tribidan§r
§0       11.04.2020§r
§0      §r
#- §1Stamina §r§0can become anything due to its existence as a medium of exchange. It is something universal, in the sense that the entire world accepts its existence and value, which is more likely to be stable. §r
#- §1Stamina§r§0 represents a common want, and to a degree, a common need from §r§4Alexandria §r§0to §r
§9Norlund§r§0. This universal importance makes it in some ways similar to religion. Both, religion and currency unite people. This, in turn, provides stability.§r
#- Another interesting aspect is where all the stamina comes from. And this topic raises phenomena supernatural. As we all know, we get 2 stamina for logging and 2.5 stamina for act called voting every 24 hours. In summary it gives us 4.5 stamina every day! 
#- In that case §4hyperinflation§r§0 would destroy economy of entire continent. §r

§0But there is another mechanic, that upholds stability and value of stamina. When you die, you loose 1 stamina§r
§0(I do not wish this to anyone). §r
#- It is like a penalty for you polluting this earth with your body. 

§0And noone thinks about it- you earn when you log in but you can loose it when you die. §r

§0Well, in fact it’s not that simple. §r
#- It is clear, that there is some §6force majeure§r
§0behind it that is collecting this penalty, and then giving back to those who died, and those who kept alive...§r
#- Even though stamina is evenly distributed, it doesn’t mean that everyone is equal in the eyes of the §6Eternal Coin§r§0 - let’s just call it this way.§r
§0Weak will die and will be punished. But Eternal Coin isn't ruthless, as it always gives a second chance.§r
#- At the other hand, those who remain won’t be rewarded, they will have a chance to multiply their funds. I suppose that is what 
§6IT§r§0 wants. We can call it a guard, who knows the quantity of existing stamina and makes sure we don't exhaust it.§r
#- In summary, Eternal Coin is just watching from aside. It leaves us independence, and what we achieve depends only on §9choices we make§r§0. Some people get rich, and some run out of stamina and have to serve a sentence.§r
#- 


